headline: EMCOR (NYSE:EME) Reports Q3 In Line With Expectations But Stock Drops 13.5%
summary: Specialty construction contractor company EMCOR (NYSE:EME) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 16.4% year on year to $4.30 billion. The company’s outlook for the full year was close to analysts’ estimates with revenue guided to $16.75 billion at the midpoint. Its GAAP profit of $6.57 per share was 0.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
